premise_source_doc_sentence: Sophie Turner  (  born 21 February 1996  )  is an English actress .

Turner made her professional acting debut as Sansa Stark on the HBO fantasy television series Game of Thrones  (  2011 -- present  )  , which brought her international recognition and critical praise .

For her performance , she has received four nominations for Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series , as well as a Young Artist Award nomination for Best Supporting Young Actress in a TV Series .
Turner has also starred in the television film The Thirteenth Tale  (  2013  )  and she made her feature film debut in Another Me  (  2013  )  .
She has also starred in the action comedy Barely Lethal  (  2015  )  and played Jean Grey / Phoenix in the X-Men film series .
